  <div class="block-3">
    <div class="inner-block">
      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Victoria Atkins MP was appointed Parliamentary Under Secretary of State at the Home Office on 9 November 2017.</p>

<p>She was elected Conservative MP for Louth and Horncastle in May 2015.</p>
</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_4430">
            <h1 id="parliamentary-under-secretary-of-state-for-crime-safeguarding-and-vulnerability">Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Crime, Safeguarding and Vulnerability</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>The minister is responsible for:</p>

<ul>
  <li>victims of terrorism</li>
  <li><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/disclosure-and-barring-service">Disclosure and Barring Service</a></li>
  <li>drugs</li>
  <li>alcohol</li>
  <li>crime prevention</li>
  <li>anti-social behaviour</li>
  <li>gangs, youth crime and youth violence</li>
  <li>knife crime</li>
  <li>wildlife crime</li>
  <li>child sexual exploitation and abuse (including <a rel="external" href="https://www.iicsa.org.uk/">Independent Inquiry into Child Sex Abuse</a>
</li>
  <li>online child sexual exploitation</li>
  <li>mental health</li>
  <li>modern slavery</li>
  <li>honour-based violence (including forced marriage and honour killings)</li>
  <li>female genital mutilation (FGM)</li>
  <li>violence against women and girls</li>
  <li>missing people and children</li>
  <li>sexual violence, prostitution and lap dancing</li>
  <li>domestic violence</li>
  <li>WEProtect</li>
  <li>internet safety</li>
</ul>
</div>
            <div class="read-more">
                <a href="/government/ministers/parliamentary-under-secretary-of-state--62">More about this role</a>
                <p class="js-hide-other-departments organisations-name-list">
  <a class="organisation-link" href="/government/organisations/home-office">Home Office</a>
</p>

            </div>
</section>          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_4587">
            <h1 id="parliamentary-under-secretary-of-state-minister-for-women">Parliamentary Under Secretary of State (Minister for Women)</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>The Minister for Women has overall responsibility for policy on gender equality.</p>
</div>
            <div class="read-more">
                <a href="/government/ministers/minister-for-women">More about this role</a>
                <p class="js-hide-other-departments organisations-name-list">
  <a class="organisation-link" href="/government/organisations/government-equalities-office">Government Equalities Office  </a> and <a class="organisation-link" href="/government/organisations/department-for-international-development">Department for International Development</a>
</p>

            </div>
</section>      </div>




